INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  'a9818966-d2da-41ce-b663-4538c87095f8',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$esbuild in a Monorepo — Workspace Packages, Shared Configs, and Turborepo Caching$escape$,
  $escape$esbuild has no native workspace awareness — you wire it up explicitly. The core pattern: set `packages: 'external'` to prevent bundling workspace siblings, then use `alias` to redirect package names to their local source or dist paths, avoiding redundant bundle passes.

For shared build configuration, export a base `BuildOptions` object from a dedicated tooling package and spread it in each package's build script. esbuild's JS API accepts plain objects, so composition is zero-cost and type-safe.

Turborepo integration is straightforward: declare a `build` task in `turbo.json` with `outputs: ["dist/**"]` and `dependsOn: ["^build"]` so upstream packages build first. Turbo's content-hash caching means unchanged packages skip esbuild entirely — the biggest win in large repos.

For watch mode, prefer esbuild's `context.watch()` JS API over the CLI flag. Instantiate one `BuildContext` per package in a root orchestrator script, sharing a single plugin registry across all contexts. This avoids spawning N separate processes.

One consistent gotcha: `tsconfig.paths` in a workspace root don't auto-resolve. Use explicit `alias` entries or `esbuild-plugin-tsconfig-paths` — esbuild won't infer them from `tsconfig.json` automatically.$escape$,
  $escape$// packages/tooling/src/build.config.ts
import type { BuildOptions } from 'esbuild';

export const baseConfig: BuildOptions = {
  bundle: true,
  platform: 'node',
  format: 'esm',
  packages: 'external',
  sourcemap: true,
};

// packages/ui/build.ts
import { build } from 'esbuild';
import { baseConfig } from '@acme/tooling/build.config';

await build({
  ...baseConfig,
  entryPoints: ['src/index.ts'],
  outdir: 'dist',
  alias: {
    '@acme/utils': '../utils/src/index.ts',
  },
});$escape$,
